 in the broader sweep of the history of science. Principe, the leading authority on the subject, recounts how Homberg’s radical vision promoted chymistry as the most powerful and reliable means of understanding the natural world. Homberg’s work at the Académie and in collaboration with the future regent, Philippe II d’Orléans, as revealed by a wealth of newly uncovered documents, provides surprising new insights into the broader changes chymistry underwent during, and immediately after, Homberg. A human, disciplinary, and institutional biography, The Transmutations of Chymistry significantly revises what was previously known about the contours of chymistry and scientific institutions in the early eighteenth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aAlchemyxHistoryy17th century. 0aAlchemyxHistoryy18th century. 0aChemistryxHistoryy17th century. 0aChemistryxHistoryy18th century. 0aChemistszFrancevBiography. 0aScientistszFrancevBiography. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aAcademie Royale des Sciences.  aWilhelm Homberg.  aalchemy.  achemistry.  ahistory of science.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2020 Englishz978311070475408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2020z9783110704556oZDB-23-DPC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUChP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069309640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226700816423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226700816.jpg  a978-3-11-069309-6  UChP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  a97